cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for abstraction and classification tasks, which are common topics in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also introduces the concept of qualitative projection, which could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
